# Targeted Verification (Concurrent-Agent Safe)

When multiple agents run concurrently, running `pnpm lint:full` or `pnpm gate:push` after every edit causes lock contention, duplicate Turborepo cache misses, and multi-minute delays. **Use the Gate Ladder (ADR-0033).**

## Gate Ladder (default — L0 after every task)

Run **`pnpm gate:help`** for the full reference. Preview L0 with **`pnpm gate:dry-run -- <paths>`** (no execution).

| Tier | When | Command | Cost |
|---|---|---|---|
| **L0** | After every edit / agent task | `pnpm gate -- <touched-paths…>` | ESLint only (seconds) |
| **L0** | Before push (app types) | `pnpm gate:typecheck` | full `tsc -b`; warm ~10–30s; cold often minutes |
| **L0** | Lint + slice typecheck | `pnpm gate -- <paths> --typecheck` | e.g. HRM → platform slice only (ADR-0042) |
| **L2** | Typed ESLint (optional) | `pnpm lint:typed -- <paths>` | `projectService`; not L0 |
| **L0** | Types only | `pnpm gate` or `pnpm typecheck` | app graph |
| **L2** | Before push / PR (human only) | `pnpm gate:push` | ~5–15 min; interactive YES |
| **L3** | Pre-merge / App Router risk (human only) | `pnpm gate:merge` | full verify + build; interactive YES |

**Never run L2/L3 after every edit.** Never run `lint:full`, `gate:push`, `build`, and `test:e2e` in one local session unless debugging CI.

### Human approval for ALL full commands (`scripts/confirm-human-full.mjs`)

**Authority: AGENTS.md §2.** Every full-repo gate requires an **interactive terminal** and typing `YES`.

Full commands (non-exhaustive): `lint` / `lint:full`, `typecheck:full`, `knip`, `test:ci`, `test:audit`, `test:coverage`, `build`, `test:e2e`, `verify*`, `gate:push`, `gate:merge`, `integrity:static`, `smoke`.

- **Agents / non-TTY shells:** **exit 2 (blocked)** — L0 only; never `AFENDA_SKIP_FULL_VERIFY_CONFIRM`.
- **CI:** `verify:ci`, workflow `build:exec` / shards — `CI=true`, no prompt.
- **One YES** covers child Turbo tasks (`AFENDA_HUMAN_FULL_CONFIRMED=1`).
- **Cursor hook:** `deny-forbidden-shell.mjs` **denies** every full command + bypass env for agent shells.

## L0 close condition (concurrent agents — use this)

```powershell
pnpm gate -- <path1> [path2 ...]
```

Before push, add app typecheck:

```powershell
pnpm gate:typecheck
# or slice-aware: pnpm gate -- <path1> [path2 ...] --typecheck
#   lib/db/** only → lib-db slice; feature paths → platform graph (skips lib/db when fresh)
```

Equivalent manual form:

```powershell
pnpm lint:path -- <path1> [path2 ...]
pnpm gate:typecheck
```

Add when those trees change:

```powershell
pnpm typecheck:test    # tests/
pnpm typecheck:scripts # scripts/
```

### Choosing ESLint paths

| What you touched | Path to pass |
|---|---|
| One file | `app/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/apps/contacts/page.tsx` |
| A feature module | `lib/features/contacts/` |
| Shell components | `components2/app-shell/` |
| Multiple dirs | `lib/features/hrm/ components2/app-shell/` |
| Whole area | `app/ lib/` (only when you touched >10 files spread across both) |

**Never pass `./` or omit paths** — that triggers full-repo ESLint (`lint:full` territory).

## When to escalate beyond L0

| Scenario | Command |
|---|---|
| Pre-push / opening a PR | `pnpm gate:push` |
| Pre-merge / route graph risk | `pnpm gate:merge` |
| Drizzle schema change | `pnpm lint:drizzle-journal` (narrow) |
| i18n message catalog change | `pnpm lint:fixtures-parity` (narrow) |
| Design token change (`globals.css`) | `pnpm lint:full` |
| Solo agent, design-token sweep only | `pnpm lint:full` — not after every feature edit |

## Command naming (ADR-0033)

| Frequency | TypeScript | ESLint |
|---|---|---|
| **Common (L0)** | `pnpm typecheck` | `pnpm lint:path -- <paths>` |
| **Full (L2+)** | `pnpm typecheck:full` | `pnpm lint:full` (alias `pnpm lint`) |

`pnpm typecheck` always resolves the full **app** graph — true per-file TS checking is not supported. The `.tsbuildinfo` cache makes it **~10s warm** vs ~60s cold. Two agents running `pnpm typecheck` simultaneously is safe (read-only); contention only arises from the `.tsbuildinfo` write at the end.

## Close condition (concurrent context)

```txt
Task is closed only when:
  pnpm gate -- <touched-paths> → exits 0
  pnpm gate:typecheck → exits 0 before push (or gate -- <paths> --typecheck in same session)
  pnpm typecheck:test / :scripts when those trees were touched
  No import targets a file that does not exist on disk
  No redirect targets a deleted route
```
